<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="140" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1387,2025]" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1387,1413]" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The new species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[706,838,1388,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Bucculatricidae" genus="Bucculatrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crataega">
<emphasis box="[706,838,1388,1413]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">B. crataega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the North American 
<taxonomicName box="[1127,1295,1387,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Bucculatricidae" genus="Bucculatrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pomifoliella">
<emphasis box="[1127,1295,1387,1413]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">B. pomifoliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the male genitalia. From 
<taxonomicName box="[332,465,1424,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Bucculatricidae" genus="Bucculatrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crataega">
<emphasis box="[332,465,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">B. crataega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the new species can be separated by: i) the strongly sclerotized and black distal part of the valva, ii) the furcated cornutus and iii) the almost semicircular vinculum; in 
<taxonomicName box="[1101,1233,1460,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Bucculatricidae" genus="Bucculatrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crataega">
<emphasis box="[1101,1233,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">B. crataega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the distal part of the valva is not as such strongly sclerotized and black (
<figureCitation box="[765,833,1495,1522]" captionStart="FIGURES 4−8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,190,1696]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,181,1709]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4−8. Male genitalia of Bucculatrix spp. 4−6, B. coadnata sp. n., holotype, slide no. SDNU.LIU0155; 4, genitalia excluding tegumen (ventral view); 5, tegumen (ventral view); 6, scale-sac. 7−8, B. crataega, holotype, SDNU.LIU0024; 7, genitalia excluding phallus (ventral view); 8, phallus. Scale bar for Figs 4, 5, 7, 8: 0.1 mm, for Fig. 6: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6127888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6127888/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), the cornutus is composed of a series of micro spines (
<figureCitation box="[160,228,1531,1558]" captionStart="FIGURES 4−8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,190,1696]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,181,1709]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4−8. Male genitalia of Bucculatrix spp. 4−6, B. coadnata sp. n., holotype, slide no. SDNU.LIU0155; 4, genitalia excluding tegumen (ventral view); 5, tegumen (ventral view); 6, scale-sac. 7−8, B. crataega, holotype, SDNU.LIU0024; 7, genitalia excluding phallus (ventral view); 8, phallus. Scale bar for Figs 4, 5, 7, 8: 0.1 mm, for Fig. 6: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6127888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6127888/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) and the vinculum is triangular on anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[827,897,1531,1558]" captionStart="FIGURES 4−8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,190,1696]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,181,1709]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4−8. Male genitalia of Bucculatrix spp. 4−6, B. coadnata sp. n., holotype, slide no. SDNU.LIU0155; 4, genitalia excluding tegumen (ventral view); 5, tegumen (ventral view); 6, scale-sac. 7−8, B. crataega, holotype, SDNU.LIU0024; 7, genitalia excluding phallus (ventral view); 8, phallus. Scale bar for Figs 4, 5, 7, 8: 0.1 mm, for Fig. 6: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6127888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6127888/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). From 
<taxonomicName box="[990,1158,1531,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Bucculatricidae" genus="Bucculatrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pomifoliella">
<emphasis box="[990,1158,1531,1557]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">B. pomifoliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the new species can be distinguished by: i) the cornutus composing of a series of micro spines and ii) the triangular vinculum (
<bibRefCitation author="Braun, A. F." pageId="3" pageNumber="140" pagination="1 - 208" refId="ref3333" refString="Braun, A. F. (1963) The genus Bucculatrix in America north of Mexico (Microlepidoptera). Memoirs of the American Entomological Society, 18, 1 - 208. [http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 118941]" type="journal article" year="1963">Braun 1963: 175</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 228).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
